+# Admin Settings audit — `/admin/settings`
+
+Static-analysis audit of every column the `app_settings` singleton row
+exposes through `PATCH /api/admin/settings`. For each field this
+document records:
+
+1. **Intent** — what the admin form labels it as / what it claims to do.
+2. **Read sites** — every place in `backend/app/` (services, routers,
+   middleware, background loops) that actually reads the value.
+3. **Effective on PATCH?** — does changing the value in the admin form
+   change real behaviour, or is it inert?
+4. **Verdict** — `WORKING`, `WORKING (conditional)`, `INERT (display
+   only)`, or `DEAD CODE`.
+
+The audit is intentionally **read-only**. Nothing in this PR changes
+functional behaviour. Recommended follow-up PRs are listed at the end.
+
+> Field set is enumerated by `_EDITABLE_FIELDS` in
+> [`backend/app/routers/admin/settings.py`](../../backend/app/routers/admin/settings.py).
+> ORM column definitions live in
+> [`backend/app/models.py`](../../backend/app/models.py) lines 654–705.
+
+---
+
+## TL;DR
+
+| Field                                   | Verdict                | Notes                                                                                     |
+| --------------------------------------- | ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
+| `deal_commission_percent`               | WORKING                | Read at `services_deals.py:311, 436, 597`.                                                |
+| `invoice_commission_percent`            | **DEAD CODE**          | No consumer anywhere in `backend/app/**`. The form persists it but nothing reads it.      |
+| `vip_commission_percent`                | WORKING (conditional)  | Applied only when `>=0` AND `buyer.is_vip or seller.is_vip` (`services_deals.py:312-314`).|
+| `min_deposit`                           | **INERT (display only)** | `services_wallet.create_deposit_invoice` enforces `currency.min_deposit`, not this column. |
+| `min_withdraw`                          | **INERT (display only)** | `services_wallet.create_withdrawal` enforces `currency.min_withdraw`, not this column.    |
+| `inactivity_pending_confirmation_days`  | WORKING                | Read by `services_deals.sweep_inactivity` (background loop).                              |
+| `inactivity_pending_cancellation_days`  | WORKING                | Read by `services_deals.sweep_inactivity` (background loop).                              |
+| `max_active_services_per_user`          | WORKING                | Read by `routers/services.py:134` SQL `func.coalesce(...)`.                               |
+| `auto_withdraw_enabled`                 | WORKING                | Read by `routers/admin/withdrawals.py:186` and `services_wallet._auto_withdraw_enabled`.  |
+| `maintenance_enabled`                   | WORKING                | Read by the `maintenance.py` middleware.                                                  |
+| `maintenance_message`                   | WORKING                | Rendered in the 503 response body of the middleware.                                      |
+
+**Three findings are user-visible problems:**
+
+- `invoice_commission_percent` is **dead** — the form accepts edits, persists
+  the value to PostgreSQL, audits the change, but **no business code
+  reads it**.
+- `min_deposit` / `min_withdraw` on the singleton row are **inert** —
+  the per-currency overrides at `Currency.min_deposit` / `Currency.min_withdraw`
+  are what the wallet routers actually enforce. The model docstring
+  acknowledges this ("global default kept around for admin display");
+  the admin form does not.
+
+See the **Recommendations** section at the end for proposed follow-up
+PRs.
+
+---
+
+## Per-field detail
+
+### `deal_commission_percent` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Обычная комиссия (сделки)».
+* **Read sites:**
+  * [`services_deals.py:311`](../../backend/app/services_deals.py) —
+    `rate = Decimal(str(settings.deal_commission_percent))` inside
+    `create_deal`. This is the canonical rate that produces
+    `Deal.commission_amount` on creation.
+  * [`services_deals.py:436`](../../backend/app/services_deals.py) —
+    fallback inside `refund_decline` for legacy deals where
+    `Deal.commission_amount` was never persisted (older rows).
+  * [`services_deals.py:597`](../../backend/app/services_deals.py) —
+    same fallback inside `refund_cancel`.
+* **Mutated by:** `PATCH /api/admin/settings` only.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Yes. New deals created after the PATCH use
+  the new rate; old deals carry their snapshotted `Deal.commission_amount`.
+* **Constraint:** model-level `CheckConstraint("deal_commission_percent BETWEEN 0 AND 100")`.
+
+### `invoice_commission_percent` — DEAD CODE
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Комиссия по счетам».
+* **Read sites:** none in production code. Specifically:
+  * `services_wallet.py` (deposit/withdraw/invoice path) — **0 matches**.
+  * `services_deals.py` — **0 matches**.
+  * `routers/wallet.py`, `routers/deals.py`, `cryptopay.py`,
+    `bot/handlers/*` — **0 matches**.
+  * `serializers.py` — **0 matches**.
+  * The only matches in `backend/app/**` are:
+    * [`models.py:668`](../../backend/app/models.py) — column declaration.
+    * [`routers/admin/settings.py:46, 73`](../../backend/app/routers/admin/settings.py) — included in `_EDITABLE_FIELDS` and `_to_out`.
+    * [`schemas.py:1986, 2006, 2019`](../../backend/app/schemas.py) — included in `AdminSettingsOut`, `AdminSettingsUpdateIn`, and the range validator.
+    * [`seed.py:117`](../../backend/app/seed.py) — initial value `0.0`.
+  * Frontend: only displayed in `AdminSettingsPage.tsx` as a `NumberField`.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** **No.** The value is persisted to PostgreSQL,
+  audited, echoed back to the form, and… ignored.
+* **History clue:** the field has been on the model since the
+  [`9d0e4d959e65_initial_schema.py`](../../alembic/versions/9d0e4d959e65_initial_schema.py)
+  migration. There is no longer any code path that would charge a
+  separate "invoice commission" — invoices for wallet top-ups go
+  through CryptoBot/Crystalpay and carry no platform fee at the moment.
+* **Risk of leaving as-is:** an operator who sets a non-zero value
+  here expects platform fees on invoices and won't get any; this is a
+  silent UX-trap.
+* **Verdict:** dead. Either wire it into the invoice creation path
+  (`services_wallet.create_deposit_invoice` / `_create_<provider>_deposit_inner`)
+  if a fee is actually wanted, or drop the column.
+
+### `vip_commission_percent` — WORKING (conditional)
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «VIP комиссия (−1 = такая же как обычная)».
+* **Read site:**
+  * [`services_deals.py:312-314`](../../backend/app/services_deals.py):
+    ```python
+    rate = Decimal(str(settings.deal_commission_percent))
+    vip_rate = Decimal(str(settings.vip_commission_percent))
+    if vip_rate >= 0 and (buyer.is_vip or seller.is_vip):
+        rate = vip_rate
+    ```
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Yes, but only for deals where **either**
+  the buyer **or** the seller carries `User.is_vip=true`. With the
+  default seed value of `-1.0` the branch is never taken.
+* **Edge cases worth flagging in UI:**
+  * The default of `-1` is a sentinel; the form label spells it out
+    («−1 = такая же как обычная») which is good.
+  * The VIP override applies if **either** party is VIP — there is
+    no separate "seller-VIP" rate.
+  * `vip_commission_percent = 0` is a real value, not a sentinel —
+    setting it to `0` makes VIP deals commission-free.
+
+### `min_deposit` (on `app_settings`) — INERT (display only)
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Мин. депозит (USD)».
+* **Apparent intent (UI):** "Global default for the minimum deposit
+  amount in USD."
+* **What actually happens:** the field is read **only** by
+  [`routers/admin/settings.py:75`](../../backend/app/routers/admin/settings.py)
+  for the form payload. The deposit-creation code path
+  ([`services_wallet.py:296-298`](../../backend/app/services_wallet.py))
+  enforces **`currency.min_deposit`**, the per-currency override:
+  ```python
+  currency = await get_currency_by_code(session, currency_code)
+  if amount < currency.min_deposit:
+      raise HTTPException(400, f"Минимальная сумма пополнения: {currency.min_deposit} {currency.code}")
+  ```
+  The model docstring at `models.py:669-676` actually spells this out
+  ("the per-currency overrides on `Currency.min_deposit` … are what
+  the wallet routers actually enforce; these singleton rows are a
+  global default kept around for admin display"), but the admin form
+  doesn't tell the operator that.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** **No.** Setting `min_deposit = 100` on the
+  singleton does not block a user from depositing 1 USDT, because
+  USDT carries its own `currency.min_deposit = 1.0` (`backend/app/seed.py:29`).
+* **Where it bleeds:** the only feedback the admin gets is via
+  `/admin/taxonomy` → «Валюты», where each currency has its own per-row
+  min-deposit field that **does** drive behaviour. The two surfaces
+  are not cross-linked.
+
+### `min_withdraw` (on `app_settings`) — INERT (display only)
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Мин. вывод (USD)».
+* **Read site:** only `routers/admin/settings.py:76` for form payload.
+* **Actual enforcer:** [`services_wallet.py:916-918`](../../backend/app/services_wallet.py)
+  uses **`currency.min_withdraw`** (the per-currency override), same
+  pattern as `min_deposit`.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** **No.** Same reason as `min_deposit`.
+
+### `inactivity_pending_confirmation_days` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Авто-истечение pending payment (дни)».
+* **Read site:**
+  [`services_deals.py:806-822`](../../backend/app/services_deals.py)
+  inside `sweep_inactivity`:
+  ```python
+  pc_cutoff = now - timedelta(days=int(settings.inactivity_pending_confirmation_days))
+  ```
+  Deals with `status == PENDING_CONFIRMATION` older than this cutoff
+  are auto-cancelled with `CANCELLED_FOR_INACTIVITY` and the buyer's
+  principal is refunded.
+* **Loop entry point:** `main.py:139-180` builds
+  `_inactivity_loop = _make_sweep_loop("inactivity", _inactivity_work, ...)`
+  and `main.py:343-344` schedules it at
+  `settings.inactivity_sweep_seconds` cadence
+  (env `INACTIVITY_SWEEP_SECONDS`, **not** an `AppSettings` field —
+  this is a separate process-level knob).
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Yes; the next loop tick re-reads the
+  setting from the DB so changes propagate within at most
+  `INACTIVITY_SWEEP_SECONDS`.
+
+### `inactivity_pending_cancellation_days` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Авто-cancellation (дни)».
+* **Read site:** `services_deals.py:818` — same loop as above, applied
+  to `status == PENDING_CANCELLATION` rows.
+* Same propagation guarantees as `inactivity_pending_confirmation_days`.
+
+### `max_active_services_per_user` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Максимум активных услуг на юзера».
+* **Read site:** [`routers/services.py:133-137`](../../backend/app/routers/services.py):
+  ```python
+  stmt = select(
+      func.coalesce(AppSettings.max_active_services_per_user, 10).label("max_active"),
+      count_stmt.label("active_count"),
+  ).limit(1)
+  ```
+  Used by `POST /api/services` to gate creation of new services
+  (the handler 409s when the user is at or above the cap).
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Yes, on the very next request — the value
+  is queried fresh per call. No caching.
+
+### `auto_withdraw_enabled` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent (form label):** «Авто-вывод через CryptoBot».
+* **Read sites:**
+  * [`services_wallet.py:867-871`](../../backend/app/services_wallet.py)
+    helper `_auto_withdraw_enabled(session)`.
+  * Direct read at
+    [`routers/admin/withdrawals.py:186`](../../backend/app/routers/admin/withdrawals.py)
+    inside the `decide` mutation. When `auto=true` **and**
+    `is_cryptopay_configured(...)`, the approve path immediately
+    issues a CryptoBot Transfer instead of leaving the withdrawal in
+    the `approved` queue for manual `mark_sent`.
+  * Second-chance fallback at
+    [`services_wallet.py:1048`](../../backend/app/services_wallet.py)
+    inside `attempt_auto_payouts` (used from deal-related flows).
+* **Toggle-time UX:** `routers/admin/settings.py:134-144` emits a
+  structured WARNING when the flag is flipped on while the
+  CryptoBot token is unset/placeholder. Good — this surfaces the
+  «silently falls back to manual» degradation in logs.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Yes, on the very next withdrawal approval.
+
+### `maintenance_enabled` + `maintenance_message` — WORKING
+
+* **Intent:** global read-only switch.
+* **Read site:** [`maintenance.py`](../../backend/app/maintenance.py)
+  middleware. The flag is cached in-process with a short TTL
+  (`_TTL_SECONDS`), invalidated explicitly by the admin PATCH
+  (`routers/admin/settings.py:201-202`) when either field is in the
+  diff.
+* **Bot side:** [`backend/app/bot/maintenance.py`](../../backend/app/bot/maintenance.py)
+  consumes the same flag for inbound Telegram updates.
+* **Effective on PATCH?** Immediately on the worker that handled the
+  PATCH; other workers / the bot process catch up within
+  `_TTL_SECONDS`.
+* **Behaviour summary:**
+  * `GET/HEAD/OPTIONS` keep working (banner overlay still rendered).
+  * Every state-changing request from a non-admin caller 503s with
+    `maintenance_message` in the body.
+  * Exception allow-list in `maintenance.py` keeps the
+    CryptoBot/Crystalpay payment webhooks reachable so paid deposits
+    don't silently churn through retries.
+
+---
+
+## Recommendations (proposed follow-up PRs)
+
+### 1. `chore/drop-invoice-commission-percent` (low risk)
+
+* Remove `AppSettings.invoice_commission_percent` end-to-end:
+  drop the column (alembic), drop from `_EDITABLE_FIELDS`,
+  drop from `AdminSettingsOut` / `AdminSettingsUpdateIn` /
+  range validator, drop from `seed.py`, drop the row from the
+  `AdminSettingsPage.tsx` UI, regenerate `openapi.generated.ts`.
+* Risk: low. The field has zero consumers, so removal is mechanical.
+* Migration:
+  ```python
+  def upgrade():
+      op.drop_column("app_settings", "invoice_commission_percent")
+
+  def downgrade():
+      op.add_column("app_settings", sa.Column(
+          "invoice_commission_percent",
+          sa.Numeric(5, 2),
+          nullable=False,
+          server_default="0.0",
+      ))
+  ```
+
+### 2. `fix/admin-settings-min-amounts-inert` (low-medium risk)
+
+Two viable paths:
+
+* **Option A — wire them in.** Make the singleton values act as a
+  floor: in `services_wallet.create_deposit_invoice`, use
+  `max(currency.min_deposit, settings.min_deposit_for(currency.code))`
+  (the singleton is USD-denominated, so this needs an FX conversion
+  or a same-currency-only check). Same for `min_withdraw`. This
+  preserves the per-currency override as the actual minimum while
+  letting the operator raise the floor globally.
+* **Option B — relabel them as display-only.** Add a help tooltip in
+  the admin form: «Это значение не используется напрямую. Реальный
+  лимит задаётся в `Валюты → <код> → Мин. депозит`». Leave the
+  column in place but rename the form label / Section to
+  «Глобальный дефолт (информационно)» and link to `/admin/taxonomy?tab=currencies`.
+
+Option B is the cheaper fix and matches what the model comment already
+documents. Option A is more honest but requires designing how the
+singleton currency (USD) interacts with non-USD currencies — this is
+a product decision, not a bug fix.
+
+### 3. `chore/admin-settings-help-text` (cosmetic)
+
+* Add short help text under each `Section` clarifying the actual
+  semantics — particularly for `vip_commission_percent`
+  («−1 — отключено, применяется когда покупатель или продавец VIP»)
+  and `auto_withdraw_enabled` («Требует валидный `CRYPTOBOT_TOKEN`,
+  иначе авто-выплаты молча падают на ручную очередь»).
+
+---
+
+## Methodology
+
+For each setting field name `X` we ran:
+
+```bash
+rg "X" backend/app frontend/src tests
+```
+
+and classified each match into one of:
+
+* **Definition / migration / seed** (model, alembic, seed.py).
+* **CRUD scaffolding** (admin settings router, admin settings schemas).
+* **Display-only frontend** (form rows, openapi types).
+* **Production consumer** (services/routers/middleware/background
+  loops that actually use the value to decide behaviour).
+
+If the union of *production consumers* is empty for a field, it is
+flagged DEAD CODE. If the only "consumer" is a different DB column
+that happens to be the actual enforcement point, the field is flagged
+INERT.
+
+No business code was modified by this audit.
